## ðŸ§± 3. Proxy Firewall with Squid

### âœ… Installation

```bash
sudo apt install squid
```

### âœ… Basic Configuration

Edit config:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/squid/squid.conf
```

Allow your network to use the proxy (replace with your IP subnet):

```conf
acl localnet src 192.168.1.0/24
http_access allow localnet
```

Set Squid to listen on internal interface:

```conf
http_port 3128
```

Restart Squid:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart squid
```

---

## âœ… Configure Client to Use Squid

On a client machine:

* Browser or system proxy settings:

  * HTTP Proxy: `192.168.1.X` (Squid server IP)
  * Port: `3128`

---

---

## ðŸ”’ Bonus: Block Sites with Squid

Edit `/etc/squid/squid.conf`:

```conf
acl blocked_sites dstdomain .facebook.com .youtube.com
http_access deny blocked_sites
```

Restart Squid:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart squid
```

